The TSCI algorithm and the functions in tsci_core.py are vendored (trimmed and
lightly adapted) from:

    KurtButler/tangentspaces  —  https://github.com/KurtButler/tangentspaces
    "Tangent Space Causal Inference: Leveraging Vector Fields for Causal
     Discovery in Dynamical Systems", Butler, Waxman & Djurić, NeurIPS 2024.
    arXiv:2410.23499

Adaptations: removed jaxtyping/tqdm/statsmodels dependencies (numpy-based ACF;
plain loops), made the optional mutual-information path (bmi) a lazy import so the
default nearest-neighbour TSCI runs on the project's main numpy-2 environment.

